article.headline: W. Michigan 64, Holy Cross 54
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Donald Lawson scored 15 points and added eight rebounds to lead Western Michigan to a 64-54 victory against Holy Cross on Saturday. Flenard Whitfield and Martelle McLemore had 10 points each for the Broncos (2-2). Mike Cavataio led Holy Cross (0-6) with 15 points. Cavataio hit two free throws to get the Crusaders to within 56-52 with 2:27 remaining. But Whitfield scored four points to give Western Michigan breathing room, and the Broncos hit their free throws in the final moments.
